snippet.textDisplay: Some really special looking players in this Celtic side julien looks like hes going to be our best defender for a long time perhaps since the time of VVD, Reiper, Balde  a solid clever defender who can score also, £7million looking like a real bargain. Frimpong? Well this bhoys got it all another goalscoring defender (needs to sharpen up on his finishing) but the speed and acceleration is unreal with his ability to run at a defence and take his man on , can turn on a sixpence and probably quite easily could play on the wing when hamed comes back . Then Edouard who oozes quality definitely destined for the rich sell out clubs. Christie, McGregor , whose not fully firing just now. I thought forster could've done better for the goal which was a good one credit when it's due. Ajer fabulous tackle. Brown imperious as ever, better even than ever? what a leader to have. Forrest. Elyounnoussi when fit again options all over the park. Look out the rest when we hit top form we have a fee more gears to go up whilst the rangers are doing well they are playing at the top of their game whilst we aren't really close to ours yet..it will be 9iar I've no doubt then 10 HH

snippet.textDisplay: The tackle was brisk but controlled and fair. Watch the slow motion replay carefully. The tackle is made with the right foot and the ball is taken cleanly whilst the ball is on the ground and by implication it wasn’t “high” - this isn’t supposed to be a golf equivalent of a “pitch” shot. Moreover, the left leg is bent at the knee and therefore it wasn’t a two-footed tackle. In any event, the contact with the left leg was minimal and took place well after the contact was made with the ball with his right foot. The rolling on the ground though and thug Brown’s usual antics likely swayed it.
